1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,119
number six, and I've titled the message this morning,

2
00:00:03,119 --> 00:00:05,900
A Life Marked by Prayer.

3
00:00:05,900 --> 00:00:07,880
A Life Marked by Prayer.

4
00:00:07,880 --> 00:00:10,239
Over the past two weeks, we've had the opportunity

5
00:00:10,239 --> 00:00:13,399
in our Sunday morning services to focus our attention

6
00:00:13,399 --> 00:00:15,720
on the subject matter of prayer.

7
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:17,840
This is week number three on the same subject,

8
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:20,159
and I said this at the end of the message last week,

9
00:00:20,159 --> 00:00:22,840
why are we focusing on prayer so much?

10
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:24,600
And I said this because I need it,

11
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,879
and I believe you need it as well.

12
00:00:26,879 --> 00:00:29,319
We need to be a praying people.

13
00:00:29,319 --> 00:00:32,919
We are thankful for the Bible truth

14
00:00:32,919 --> 00:00:36,439
that God has extended to each of us an invitation

15
00:00:36,439 --> 00:00:40,599
to enter into his presence at any time for any reason,

16
00:00:40,599 --> 00:00:43,880
and we have direct access to the throne of grace.

17
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:47,000
We are to come boldly unto that throne.

18
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,340
And what a wonderful privilege prayer is,

19
00:00:50,340 --> 00:00:55,340
but I find today that so often prayer is neglected,

20
00:00:55,959 --> 00:00:57,639
and we need to understand,

21
00:00:57,639 --> 00:00:59,919
we need to be people of prayer.

22
00:00:59,919 --> 00:01:03,439
Our lives need to be marked by prayer.

23
00:01:03,439 --> 00:01:06,879
We've had the opportunity in these last couple of weeks

24
00:01:06,879 --> 00:01:08,819
to be able to look at the life of David,

25
00:01:08,819 --> 00:01:10,860
and also at the life of Daniel,

26
00:01:10,860 --> 00:01:14,080
and taking some snippets, if you will, from their lives,

27
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:19,040
and consider their example of men that were praying men.

28
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:22,680
I believe that how we pray, how you pray, and how I pray,

29
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:27,279
is greatly impacted by what we believe to be true

30
00:01:27,319 --> 00:01:28,480
about God.

31
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:32,120
If we didn't believe this morning that God hears prayer,

32
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:35,480
there'd be no reason to pray, amen?

33
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:37,599
But God has told us in his word,

34
00:01:37,599 --> 00:01:39,800
he has revealed the truth to us in his word,

35
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,559
that he hears prayer.

36
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:44,680
And not only does he hear prayer, but he answers prayer,

37
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:48,879
and so what we believe to be true about God

38
00:01:48,879 --> 00:01:52,160
will greatly impact how we pray.

39
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:56,239
What is true about God is revealed to us in his word.

40
00:01:56,239 --> 00:01:58,919
It's not just what you think to be true about God,

41
00:01:58,919 --> 00:02:02,319
it's what God has revealed to us through his precious word

42
00:02:02,319 --> 00:02:04,720
with regard to who he is,

43
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:09,000
and that truth that we find with regard to who our God is

44
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,399
should impact every area of our lives.

45
00:02:12,399 --> 00:02:17,119
How we live should be impacted by what we believe.

46
00:02:17,119 --> 00:02:19,960
Our behavior is impacted by our belief.

47
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:23,520
And we find this morning as we continue with this thought

48
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:25,559
of the subject matter of prayer,

49
00:02:25,559 --> 00:02:29,160
I hope this morning that each of us would consider

50
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:32,119
not only the example from David in Psalm 34,

51
00:02:32,119 --> 00:02:34,740
the example of Daniel in Daniel chapter number two,

52
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:37,240
but this morning as we look at Ephesians chapter number six,

53
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:39,639
and just very honest with you this morning,

54
00:02:39,639 --> 00:02:41,880
we're gonna be at a number of different passages

55
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:45,720
of scripture, primarily right here within the epistles

56
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:47,800
that we find, the Pauline epistles,

57
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,960
and so we're gonna look at a number of verses of scripture,

58
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:53,160
but I want you to consider the life of Paul this morning.

59
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,360
There are a lot of things that we could say

60
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:57,039
about the Apostle Paul, but I believe this morning

61
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:58,919
that one thing that we could say that would be true

62
00:02:58,919 --> 00:03:02,039
of the Apostle Paul is that he was a man

63
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:04,559
that his life was marked by prayer.

64
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:05,759
His life was marked by prayer.

65
00:03:05,759 --> 00:03:07,000
You begin to read the epistles.

66
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,559
You begin to read, and we understand that all scripture

67
00:03:09,559 --> 00:03:11,240
is given by inspiration of God.

68
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:13,679
We understand that God is the author of scripture,

69
00:03:13,679 --> 00:03:18,679
but we find that he, God, used the Apostle Paul, this man,

70
00:03:19,559 --> 00:03:21,199
to be able to be the human penman

71
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:22,880
for a lot of our New Testament.

72
00:03:22,919 --> 00:03:23,960
And we have the opportunity,

73
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:25,600
as we read through the Pauline epistles,

74
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:29,240
and we read the letters, and we begin to get the sense

75
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:33,279
of this is a man whose life was marked by prayer.

76
00:03:33,279 --> 00:03:35,119
Notice in Ephesians chapter number six,

77
00:03:35,119 --> 00:03:36,639
we're familiar with the portion of scripture.

78
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:38,559
I have in the bulletin just verse number 18,

79
00:03:38,559 --> 00:03:40,520
but I wanna catch it all in context.

80
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,119
Begin reading with me in verse number 10.

81
00:03:42,119 --> 00:03:43,800
In Ephesians chapter number six,

82
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,320
notice what the Apostle Paul says

83
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,000
to the believers of the church at Ephesus

84
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,160
under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God.

85
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:53,240
Finally, my brethren, be strong in the Lord

86
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,720
in the power of his might.

87
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:57,199
Put on the whole armor of God that you may be able to stand

88
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:58,919
against the wiles of the devil.

89
00:03:58,919 --> 00:04:01,639
For we wrestle not against flesh and blood,

90
00:04:01,639 --> 00:04:04,660
but against principalities, against powers,

91
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:07,039
against the rulers of the darkness of this world,

92
00:04:07,039 --> 00:04:11,039
against spiritual wickedness in high places.

93
00:04:11,039 --> 00:04:12,199
How many of you know this morning

94
00:04:12,199 --> 00:04:14,679
that we're engaged in spiritual warfare?

95
00:04:14,679 --> 00:04:17,480
I think it was Torrey, he said the spiritual life,

96
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:19,640
the Christian life can best be described

97
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:22,519
not as a playground, but as a battleground.

98
00:04:22,519 --> 00:04:26,640
And certainly we are engaged in spiritual warfare.

99
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,920
It's all around us.

100
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:30,239
And so Paul continues to say this,

101
00:04:30,239 --> 00:04:31,640
wherefore in verse number 13,

102
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:35,200
take unto you the whole armor of God

103
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:38,720
that you may be able to withstand in the evil day

104
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:41,600
and having done all to stand.

105
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:45,359
Stand therefore, having your loins girt about with truth

106
00:04:45,359 --> 00:04:48,320
and having on the breastplate of righteousness

107
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,239
and your feet shod with the preparation

108
00:04:50,239 --> 00:04:51,839
of the gospel of peace,

109
00:04:51,839 --> 00:04:54,320
above all taking the shield of faith

110
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,880
wherewith you shall be able to quench

111
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:58,320
all the fiery darts of the wicked

112
00:04:58,320 --> 00:05:00,119
and take the helmet of salvation

113
00:05:00,119 --> 00:05:03,399
and the sword of the spirit, which is the word of God.

114
00:05:03,399 --> 00:05:06,160
Then notice verse 18, Paul says this,

115
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:09,640
praying always with all prayer and supplication

116
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:12,200
in the spirit and watching there unto

117
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:15,040
with all perseverance and supplication

118
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,559
for all saints.

119
00:05:16,559 --> 00:05:19,440
And for me, that utterance may be given unto me

120
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:21,959
that I may open my mouth boldly

121
00:05:21,959 --> 00:05:25,200
to make known the mystery of the gospel

122
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,600
for which I am an ambassador in bonds

123
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:32,600
that therein I may speak boldly as I ought to speak.

124
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:35,799
A man, the apostle Paul, he's a man just like you and I are.

125
00:05:35,799 --> 00:05:36,920
Sometimes if we're not careful,

126
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:40,799
we elevate the apostle Paul to a place of such level

127
00:05:40,799 --> 00:05:43,559
that really he would not desire for any of us

128
00:05:43,559 --> 00:05:45,000
to elevate him to.

129
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:46,679
I believe that the apostle Paul,

130
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:48,359
though he's not the one that wrote the words,

131
00:05:48,359 --> 00:05:52,600
John the Baptist says I must decrease and he must increase,

132
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,200
but I believe the apostle Paul

133
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:56,040
in 2 Corinthians chapter number 12,

134
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:58,559
he makes it obvious that he doesn't want others

135
00:05:58,559 --> 00:06:01,480
to think more highly of him than they ought.

136
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,640
And I believe that Paul,

137
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:05,079
he demonstrates throughout his writings

138
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:07,119
that he was a man that sought to be humble

139
00:06:07,119 --> 00:06:09,720
and understood the work that Christ did

140
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,359
in and through his life.

141
00:06:11,359 --> 00:06:14,720
At times, however, we might elevate the apostle Paul

142
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,600
to a level, again, that he would not desire

143
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:20,200
for us to elevate him to.

144
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,440
But I think about the apostle Paul this morning

145
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:24,959
and I look at these various portions of scripture

146
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:26,799
that we'll look to and I find a man

147
00:06:26,799 --> 00:06:29,000
who is a man just like we are.

148
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,320
He's made of the flesh just like we are,

149
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:34,000
yet he was saved by the grace of God

150
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,519
and what a transformation.

151
00:06:35,519 --> 00:06:37,519
God used him to write this truth,

152
00:06:37,519 --> 00:06:40,679
if any man be in Christ, he is a new creature.

153
00:06:40,679 --> 00:06:41,880
Old things are passed away,

154
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,839
behold, all things are become new.

155
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,519
And we find that the apostle Paul was a man

156
00:06:46,519 --> 00:06:48,640
who was zealous for the Lord.

157
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:51,679
He was a man that was, I believe, surrendered

158
00:06:51,679 --> 00:06:54,079
to the Lord and to the Lord's will.

159
00:06:54,079 --> 00:06:56,200
He's a man that God used greatly

160
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:58,399
and at times we could examine the scripture and say,

161
00:06:58,399 --> 00:07:01,239
why did God use the apostle Paul

162
00:07:01,239 --> 00:07:02,720
in the fashion in which he did?

163
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:05,000
And I believe the answer is very simple,

164
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,839
that the apostle Paul was fully surrendered

165
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:09,000
to the will of God.

166
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,920
He said, I am crucified with Christ.

167
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:15,399
He was willing to do whatever the Lord wanted him to do

168
00:07:15,399 --> 00:07:18,679
and his life is a life that's marked by prayer.

169
00:07:18,679 --> 00:07:20,200
As we look at the text of scripture

170
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,880
and we consider a variety of portions

171
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:22,760
of scripture this morning,

172
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,200
I want you to consider this,

173
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:26,399
a life that is marked by prayer,

174
00:07:26,399 --> 00:07:27,959
three thoughts, number one,

175
00:07:27,959 --> 00:07:31,239
there must be a commitment to prayer,

176
00:07:31,239 --> 00:07:32,679
a commitment to prayer.

177
00:07:32,679 --> 00:07:33,519
What do I mean by that?

178
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:35,600
Well, as we look at the portion of scripture

179
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,440
and we'll look at some verses

180
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:38,160
as we get through the message this morning,

181
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,519
I believe that the apostle Paul

182
00:07:39,519 --> 00:07:42,279
was personally committed to prayer.

183
00:07:42,279 --> 00:07:44,480
Not only was he personally committed to prayer,

184
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:47,640
but he also encouraged and instructed others

185
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,160
to be people of prayer.

186
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:51,720
He understood, the apostle Paul understood

187
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,480
the importance of making this commitment.

188
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:55,880
We find today that we live in a society

189
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:59,320
where commitments are maybe not as binding

190
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,279
as they once were,

191
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:02,799
where people will break their word and what have you,

192
00:08:02,799 --> 00:08:05,720
but I want you to think about being committed to something

193
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,160
and there are some people that are committed

194
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,959
to a variety of causes and a variety of things,

195
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:11,480
but I want you to think about the importance

196
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:14,000
of making a commitment to prayer.

197
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:18,000
See, God has ordained it that prayer moves the hand of God.

198
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:22,239
Prayer moves the hand of God.

199
00:08:22,239 --> 00:08:24,519
God said to Jeremiah, call unto me

200
00:08:24,519 --> 00:08:28,760
and I will answer thee and show thee great and mighty things

201
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,200
which thou knowest not.

202
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,920
And so God has ordained it

203
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,039
that we would be people of prayer

204
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:36,880
and we must have a commitment to prayer.

205
00:08:37,599 --> 00:08:39,039
In other words, it's not just a situation

206
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:40,919
of if I have time, I'll pray.

207
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:42,479
Let me say this, if that's your approach,

208
00:08:42,479 --> 00:08:44,239
you're not gonna ever pray.

209
00:08:44,239 --> 00:08:45,080
Why?

210
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,679
Because you're never gonna have time.

211
00:08:46,679 --> 00:08:47,960
There's always gonna be something else

212
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,320
that's vying for your time.

213
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,559
There's something else that's gonna fill your time

214
00:08:51,559 --> 00:08:54,840
and so there must be a commitment that we make

215
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,599
and I believe that the apostle Paul

216
00:08:56,599 --> 00:08:58,280
made a commitment to prayer.

217
00:08:58,280 --> 00:09:01,039
There's no doubt that his commitment to prayer

218
00:09:01,039 --> 00:09:04,200
was a result of what he understood to be true

219
00:09:04,239 --> 00:09:07,000
about God and about the subject matter of prayer

220
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,239
as revealed in the Old Testament.

221
00:09:09,239 --> 00:09:10,479
Understand with me this morning

222
00:09:10,479 --> 00:09:13,239
that the apostle Paul was a man that was well trained.

223
00:09:13,239 --> 00:09:15,599
The apostle Paul was a man that was well acquainted

224
00:09:15,599 --> 00:09:17,239
with the truth of the Old Testament.

225
00:09:17,239 --> 00:09:21,280
He was a man that was really a leader.

226
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:24,320
He was a man that was sitting at the feet of Gamaliel.

227
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:26,320
He says that he was a Pharisee of the Pharisees

228
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:29,599
and he had been trained and the Old Testament understood it

229
00:09:29,599 --> 00:09:31,080
and I believe this morning

230
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:33,640
that when you begin to look at the life of the apostle Paul

231
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:37,359
after his conversion in Acts chapter number nine

232
00:09:37,359 --> 00:09:41,520
and you see the way in which he was taught by the Lord

233
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,520
and the instruction he received,

234
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:46,479
we find that he was a man that was committed to prayer.

235
00:09:46,479 --> 00:09:49,000
He was familiar with the Old Testament records

236
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,640
of the subject of prayer.

237
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,599
The last two weeks, we've had the opportunity

238
00:09:52,599 --> 00:09:55,119
to look at some of those examples of prayer

239
00:09:55,119 --> 00:09:57,719
in the life of David and also in the life of Daniel

240
00:09:57,719 --> 00:09:58,799
but I want you to understand

241
00:09:58,799 --> 00:10:00,799
that if you were to go through the Old Testament,

242
00:10:00,799 --> 00:10:04,799
something that you'll find is you'll find a lot of recorded prayers.

243
00:10:04,799 --> 00:10:08,799
You'll find a lot of God's people, heroes of the faith,

244
00:10:08,799 --> 00:10:10,799
that were people of prayer.

245
00:10:10,799 --> 00:10:13,799
And their prayers are recorded for us in the Old Testament.

246
00:10:13,799 --> 00:10:16,799
You can read them, you can go and you can read

247
00:10:16,799 --> 00:10:19,799
of the prayers of those servants of the Lord

248
00:10:19,799 --> 00:10:22,799
as they're recorded for us in the Old Testament.

249
00:10:22,799 --> 00:10:24,799
You think about the way in which the New Testament

250
00:10:24,799 --> 00:10:26,799
would reference back even to the Old Testament.

251
00:10:26,799 --> 00:10:29,799
It's the Apostle Paul that says that those things

252
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:32,799
that were written aforetime were written for our admonition,

253
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:34,799
they were written for our instruction,

254
00:10:34,799 --> 00:10:37,799
and we find that the Apostle Paul was very aware,

255
00:10:37,799 --> 00:10:39,799
he was very familiar with the Old Testament,

256
00:10:39,799 --> 00:10:41,799
and so he would have been aware of the recorded prayers.

257
00:10:41,799 --> 00:10:45,799
Think about James, he references the prayer of Elijah,

258
00:10:45,799 --> 00:10:47,799
the effectual, fervent prayer of a righteous man.

259
00:10:47,799 --> 00:10:49,799
