that you would know the will of God, that you would do the will of God, that you would

974
00:47:07,179 --> 00:47:13,419
be strengthened with divine strength so that you could do what God has called you to do.

975
00:47:13,419 --> 00:47:17,500
So when I look at a life that's marked by prayer, I look at the life of the Apostle

976
00:47:17,500 --> 00:47:23,379
Paul. Are there other examples that we could look to? Sure, there are. But this morning

977
00:47:23,379 --> 00:47:30,099
as we spend this time focused on a life that's marked by prayer, the life of the Apostle

978
00:47:30,099 --> 00:47:36,859
Paul, we see a man who is committed to prayer. I wonder this morning, what kind of commitment

979
00:47:36,859 --> 00:47:44,899
do we have to prayer? Is our commitment to prayer stronger than our commitment to the

980
00:47:44,899 --> 00:47:49,979
gym? I'm just going to throw it right out there. You know, there are some people that

981
00:47:49,979 --> 00:47:55,139
are so committed to the gym that they just will not miss. It doesn't matter how long

982
00:47:55,139 --> 00:47:58,979
the day went, it doesn't matter how many meetings they had that they didn't expect, how many

983
00:47:58,979 --> 00:48:04,019
things got changed, they're going to the gym because they have a commitment. I wonder what

984
00:48:04,019 --> 00:48:10,379
our commitment is to prayer. I mean, God hears and answers. God has ordained that prayer

985
00:48:10,379 --> 00:48:19,579
moves the hand of God. Is there consistency in our prayer life? I mean, are we consistent?

986
00:48:19,579 --> 00:48:26,859
I wonder this morning, what's the content of our prayer? Are we praying with a spiritual

987
00:48:26,859 --> 00:48:34,739
emphasis or are we just praying kind of on this temporal plane? I hope this morning that

988
00:48:34,739 --> 00:48:38,700
just as we said of the Apostle Paul, that his life is a life that's marked by prayer,

989
00:48:38,700 --> 00:48:43,099
I believe that those people that Paul ministered to, those people that Paul interacted with,

990
00:48:43,099 --> 00:48:48,659
they knew that he was a man of prayer. He was committed to it. I wonder this morning,

991
00:48:48,659 --> 00:48:57,059
how many people know of us? That's a prayer warrior. That's a man, a woman, a young person

992
00:48:57,059 --> 00:49:04,099
of prayer. A life marked by prayer. Let's pray. Father, we love you. Thank you for loving

993
00:49:04,099 --> 00:49:09,619
us. Thank you for the opportunity to examine your Word this morning, to be challenged.

994
00:49:09,619 --> 00:49:19,260
God, you've challenged me in this area of prayer as I've prepared, then again as I delivered.

995
00:49:19,260 --> 00:49:25,619
Lord, I pray that you would challenge each of us in this area of prayer. I pray that

996
00:49:25,619 --> 00:49:32,019
we'd be honest and humble before you as we truly examine our lives, our prayer lives.

997
00:49:32,019 --> 00:49:36,019
I pray that what we believe to be true about you, what we find in your Word with regard

998
00:49:36,059 --> 00:49:41,219
to who you are and what you're capable of doing, I pray that that would shape, impact

999
00:49:41,219 --> 00:49:47,380
our prayer lives. Lord, I pray that if there's one that's not saved, that today would be

1000
00:49:47,380 --> 00:49:52,339
the day of their salvation. They've never trusted Christ. They don't have assurance

1001
00:49:52,339 --> 00:49:55,539
that if they were to die today, they'd go to heaven. God, I pray that you'd give us

1002
00:49:55,539 --> 00:49:58,700
an opportunity to take a Bible and show them how they could know for sure without any doubt

1003
00:49:58,700 --> 00:50:01,419
whatsoever, not because of anything they could do, but...

1004
00:50:01,419 --> 00:50:06,859
because of what the Lord Jesus Christ did, God in flesh on the cross of Calvary, His

1005
00:50:06,859 --> 00:50:07,859
glorious resurrection.

1006
00:50:07,859 --> 00:50:14,459
Would you give us that opportunity this morning to see someone trust Christ?

1007
00:50:14,459 --> 00:50:18,479
I pray that as we examine our prayer lives that we do business with you in these moments

1008
00:50:18,479 --> 00:50:19,479
of invitation.

1009
00:50:19,479 --> 00:50:26,059
I pray that we wouldn't rush, Lord, but we'd allow you to have your way in our lives, that

1010
00:50:26,059 --> 00:50:31,859
we'd be responsive, that we'd be doers of the Word.

1011
00:50:31,859 --> 00:50:34,899
Bless now as only you can and we'll thank you for all that you'll do, for it's in Christ's

1012
00:50:34,899 --> 00:50:35,899
name we pray.

1013
00:50:35,899 --> 00:50:36,899
Would you stand with me?

1014
00:50:36,899 --> 00:50:39,459
Heads are bowed, eyes are closed.

1015
00:50:39,459 --> 00:50:43,899
Kimberly's going to play quietly on the piano, and as she does, the altar is open.

